OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCovid blamed for drop in   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fyoung Welsh speakers       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Covid lockdowns have been partly blamed
OL,6, for a drop in young Welsh speakers, who
OL,7, were not able to use the language      
OL,8, regularly for two years.               
OL,10,FThe 2021 census showed a 5.7% drop in  
OL,11,Fthe number of school-age children able 
OL,12,Fto speak Welsh since 2011.             
OL,14,FThis is despite the numbers in         
OL,15,FWelsh-medium education rising in that  
OL,16,Fperiod by 11,000 pupils.               
OL,18,FStudents in a Welsh-speaking heartland 
OL,19,Fbelieve Covid may have hit the         
OL,20,Fconfidence of some to use it socially. 
